Habit Coach AI

LINK FOR VIDEO DEMO: https://youtu.be/R0gZbgmhgis
LINK FOR ARCHITECTURE DIAGRAM: https://www.figma.com/make/sIHqt3h2Z16zKTgGj2O2kT/Create-AI-Search-Diagram?p=f&t=Dot4IQuq9QEOD0Sy-0

An AI-powered habit and productivity coach that helps users build better habits, stay accountable, and achieve their goals through personalized guidance and progress tracking.

Features
- AI Habit Coach:
Chat with an AI assistant for motivation and advice.
Receive personalized suggestions via daily notifications based on your habits and goals.
- Task & Habit Management:
Create daily habits and tasks.
Mark habits as completed.
Track streaks and consistency.
- Progress Tracking:
Visualize progress over time.
Monitor completed habits and achievements.
- Goal Setting:
Break goals into manageable habits.
Customizable Experience:
Notification preferences
Dark/light mode
Personalized coaching style

Motivation:
Building habits is difficult, and many people struggle to stay consistent. Habit Coach AI
was created to provide users with an intelligent and supportive assistant that not
only tracks habits but also offers encouragement, accountability, and actionable
advice tailored to their goals.
The aim is to combine habit tracking with AI to make self-improvement
more engaging and effective.

Tech Stack:
Frontend: Android (Java), XML layouts
Knowledge Layer (Foundry IQ Engine): Azure AI Search with Semantic Ranker enabled
Storage Layer: Azure Blob Storage (for holding coach guidelines and document data)
LLM Reasoning Brain: OpenAI gpt-4o-mini accessed via the Azure AI Inference SDK

Tools:
Android Studio, Git & GitHub, Azure AI Inference SDK for Java, Azure AI Search SDK, GitHub Copilot, Figma (for design)

How It Works:
The user creates habits and goals.
Habits are tracked daily.
The AI coach analyzes progress and user input.
Personalized recommendations and motivational messages are generated.
Users review their progress and continue improving through a streaks page.
The user creates habits and logs progress.

Example Use Cases:
Build a daily study routine.
Develop healthier habits.
Stay accountable for fitness goals.
Improve productivity and time management.
Receive AI-powered motivation when struggling to stay consistent.

Setup & Installation
1. Clone this repository to your local machine.
2. Open the project in Android Studio.
3. Ensure you have internet permissions enabled in your `AndroidManifest.xml`.
4. Sync the Gradle project to download the Azure Inference and Search SDK dependencies.
5. Add your Azure AI Search Endpoint, Primary Admin Key, Index Name, and GitHub Token to your configuration file.
    1. Create a file named `secrets.properties` in the root directory of the project.
    2. Add the following keys with your specific deployment coordinates:
       SEARCH_ENDPOINT="https://<your-search-service>.search.windows.net"
       SEARCH_KEY="<your-azure-admin-key>"
       INDEX_NAME="<your-index-name>"
       GITHUB_TOKEN="<your-github-models-token>"
6. Build and run the application on an emulator or physical Android device.
